3.00	Polyhydroxyethylmethacrylate	Polyhydroxyethylmethacrylate	Poly(2-hydroxyethyl methacrylate) is a polymer that forms a hydrogel in water. It was invented by Drahoslav Lim for use in soft contact lenses. Copolymers of pHEMA are still widely used today.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7e/Polyhydroxyethylmethacrylate_structural.svg/220px-Polyhydroxyethylmethacrylate_structural.svg.png
